In August 2023, PlayCyberGames which "allows users to play any games with LAN function or games using IP address" suffered
a data breach which exposed 3.7M customer records. The data included email addresses, usernames and MD5 password hashes with
a constant value in the "salt" field. PlayCyberGames did not respond to multiple attempts to disclose the breach.

View:
https://direct-link.net/68451/playcybergames-database-l
